A4.text: The Iraqi invasion of Kuwait, codenamed Project 17, began on 2 August 1990 and marked the beginning of the Gulf War.

A5.text: After defeating the State of Kuwait on 4 August 1990, Iraq went on to militarily occupy the country for the next seven months.
